--><p><a class="post_image_link" href="http://www.artfagcity.com/2012/09/18/art-copenhagen-takes-steps-in-a-new-direction/" title="Permanent link to Art Copenhagen Takes Steps in a New Direction"><img class="post_image alignleft" src="http://static.artfagcity.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/180-copenhagen-.jpeg" width="180" height="112" alt="Post image for Art Copenhagen Takes Steps in a New Direction" /></a>
</p>
<p><a href="http://static.artfagcity.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/copenhagen.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full-width-ratio wp-image-42717" title="copenhagen" src="http://static.artfagcity.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/copenhagen-640x480.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="480" /></a></p>
<p>There&#8217;s no escaping New York. Ten minutes after arriving at <a href="http://www.artcopenhagen.dk/" target="_blank">Art Copenhagen</a> on Sunday, we encountered our boss Paddy Johnson&#8217;s face in William Powhida&#8217;s <em>Cosmology</em> (2010), a zodiac chart dividing New York art world figures into destroyers, saints, and so forth, with captions describing their roles.</p>
